TY  - JOUR
T1  - Comments on “Economic Ordering Frequency for Two Items Jointly Replenished” by Frank T. Shu
AU  - Kalro, Amarlal H.
Y1  - 1972/08/01
PY  - 1972
DA  - 1972/08/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.18.12.B732
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.18.12.B732
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - B-732
EP  - B-733
VL  - 18
IS  - 12
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - In his paper (Management Science, Vol. 17, No. 6, pp. B-406?B-410) Shu describes a method for determining the replenishment frequencies of items jointly replenished. Essentially, the procedure develops ?skipping rules? for an item, this being replenished every kth time that the others are replenished. A better procedure is to rank the items in decreasing order of demand/set-up cost ratio, then select the lowest ratio item as the skipped item.
AB  - In his paper (Management Science, Vol. 17, No. 6, pp. B-406?B-410) Shu describes a method for determining the replenishment frequencies of items jointly replenished. Essentially, the procedure develops ?skipping rules? for an item, this being replenished every kth time that the others are replenished. A better procedure is to rank the items in decreasing order of demand/set-up cost ratio, then select the lowest ratio item as the skipped item.
